## Models & Relationships

```
User (1) --- (1) Patient (1) --- (*) Appointment
WorkingHour (standalone)
CmsAbout (standalone)
Course (standalone)
Video (standalone)
Certification (standalone)
Post (standalone)
```

- **User:** HasApiTokens, HasOne(Patient), isAdmin()/isPatient() checkers
- **Patient:** BelongsTo(User), HasMany(Appointment), date casts
- **Appointment:** BelongsTo(Patient), status casts to AppointmentStatus, date casts
- All CMS models: is_active boolean, sort_order integer

---

## Notifications & Broadcasting Flow

1. Admin updates appointment status (BookingController@updateStatus)
2. AppointmentStatusUpdated event is broadcast via Pusher to channel `appointments.{patientId}`
3. AppointmentStatusNotification is stored in DB (Laravel notifications table)
4. AppointmentApprovedMail or AppointmentRejectedMail is sent via SMTP

---

## SlotService Logic

- SLOT_DURATION_MINUTES = 60
- Fetches active working hours for requested day_of_week
- Generates 60-minute slots from start_time to end_time
- Removes slots overlapping with existing pending/approved appointments
- Returns available slots with time + availability status

---

